        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 11:10PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 1110 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hamilton, or near Keokuk, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Ferris and Carthage around 1115 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
